sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Controller
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(Scheduler + Preemption)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(OpenShift Monitoring)
    participant RemoteAPI as Remote Worker Cluster API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: Workload Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: Create Job/PyTorchJob/RayJob<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating webhook call<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject queue label<br/>Suspend workload<br/>Set managedBy field
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated resource
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validating webhook call<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate queue name<br/>Check TAS annotations<br/>Enforce constraints
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission response
    K8sAPI-->>User: Resource created (suspended)

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Controller reconciliation loop

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Workload CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: New Workload event
    Controller->>Controller: Schedule: find ClusterQueue<br/>Check quota (nominal + borrowing)<br/>Assign ResourceFlavor
    alt Quota available
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Workload admission<br/>Unsuspend Job<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Workload admitted
    else Quota exhausted - preemption needed
        Controller->>Controller: Evaluate preemption candidates<br/>(LowerPriority / LowerOrNewerEqual / Any)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Evict lower-priority workloads<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Admit current workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    else Quota exhausted - no preemption possible
        Controller->>Controller: Queue workload (pending)<br/>StrictFIFO or BestEffortFIFO
    end

    Note over Controller,RemoteAPI: Flow 2: MultiKueue Distribution (when enabled)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read Workload with MultiKueue AdmissionCheck<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read MultiKueueCluster Secret (kubeconfig)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>RemoteAPI: Create shadow Workload on worker cluster<br/>Auth: KubeConfig credentials (from Secret)
    RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Workload status updates
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update local Workload status<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Admission, quota, scheduling,<br/>queue metrics (Prometheus format)
